01:00:39,521 --> 01:00:47,801
Perhaps the slanting sunlight and the holy image to which his poor mother had held him up still worked upon his imagination.

662
01:00:47,800 --> 01:01:02,121
So there's something in that whole scene, the love of his mother and her dedication of him, so to speak, to the icon, to the Virgin Mary, and so forth, which made a lasting impression on him.

663
01:01:02,121 --> 01:01:12,841
And the first example there more coming up of how it made a lasting impression on him was that the slanting rays of the sun play an interesting role.

664
01:01:13,161 --> 01:01:19,240
I just tell you a hint, but somehow the slanting rays of the sun are the nearest thing you get to God in the book.

