749
01:09:04,201 --> 01:09:11,400
Ordination of priests, the crucifixion, immortality, angels, and devils.

750
01:09:11,401 --> 01:09:13,880
All of them get existentialized.

751
01:09:13,880 --> 01:09:19,320
And even, and this is the most fun in the book, if you're liking this kind of thing, miracles.

752
01:09:19,321 --> 01:09:25,561
You'd think you could hardly do it with miracles, since miracles seem to be the things that go against physics and chemistry.

753
01:09:25,561 --> 01:09:36,400
But he's going to save the existential meaning of miracles in a way that has nothing to do with the laws that govern the way the world works.

754
01:09:36,401 --> 01:09:41,840
And when he does, and you keep your eyes open for it, he's going to tell you that was a miracle.

755
01:09:42,481 --> 01:09:44,080
Because he's always telling you that.

756
01:09:44,080 --> 01:09:45,040
Go ahead, Beatrice.

